{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Santiago Ferreira","author":"Santiago Ferreira"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"42f04d46-b11c-5dc5-bf93-c067e9858593","excerpt":"Simplify the process of creating universal React Native applicationsAfter working with Styled Components and Styled System for web, I realized I needed…","html":"<h3>Simplify the process of creating universal React Native applications</h3>\n<p>After working with <strong>Styled Components</strong> and <strong>Styled System</strong> for web, I realized I needed something similar for <strong>React Native</strong>. At the time I didn’t find good alternatives so I decided to build <strong>Reflect</strong>. Besides being a style system, <strong>Reflect</strong> also has methods to make the process of creating layouts and UI for universal apps more intuitive and succinct.</p>\n<p><strong>Reflect</strong> is fully documented and unit tested:</p>\n<h4>Main Links</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://sntx.github.io/react-native-reflect\">Documentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sntx/react-native-reflect\">GitHub</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Tutorials</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://dev.to/sntx/build-a-responsive-react-native-photo-album-part-1-4doe\">Responsive UX Design with React Native Reflect (Part 1)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dev.to/sntx/responsive-ux-design-with-react-native-reflect-part-2-m24\">Responsive UX Design with React Native Reflect (Part 2)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dev.to/sntx/responsive-ux-design-with-react-native-reflect-part-3-2i6f\">Responsive UX Design with React Native Reflect (Part 3)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dev.to/sntx/responsive-ux-design-with-react-native-reflect-part-4-14e4\">Responsive UX Design with React Native Reflect (Part 4)</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"React Native Reflect","date":"June 08, 2019","description":"Responsive, theme-based style system for React Native","technologies":null,"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:im